{
  "texts": [
    "1b for the directional diversity collapse when fine-tuning Llama-2-7B.",
    "To address this pathology, we put forth PoLAR, a co-design of architecture and optimizer that mitigates the directional diversity collapse, as shown in Fig. 1c.",
    "On the architecture side, PoLAR facilitates effective exploitation of the linear algebraic rank by expressing the low-rank update as the product of two column-orthogonal direction matrices and a r × r scale matrix.",
    "This parameterization can also be interpreted from the perspective of decoupling direction and magnitude, which arises naturally when the low-rank factors are lifted via the polar decomposition.",
    "On the optimizer side, we apply methods from Riemannian optimization (Boumal, 2023)."
  ]
}